[
  {
    "startTime": 16.26,
    "endTime": 20.26,
    "text": "So I was privileged to train in transplantation"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 20.26,
    "endTime": 22.26,
    "text": "under two great surgical pioneers:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 22.26,
    "endTime": 24.26,
    "text": "Thomas Starzl,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 24.26,
    "endTime": 27.26,
    "text": "who performed the world's first successful liver transplant"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 27.26,
    "endTime": 29.26,
    "text": "in 1967,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 29.26,
    "endTime": 31.26,
    "text": "and Sir Roy Calne,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 31.26,
    "endTime": 34.260000000000005,
    "text": "who performed the first liver transplant in the U.K."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 34.26,
    "endTime": 37.26,
    "text": "in the following year."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 37.26,
    "endTime": 39.26,
    "text": "I returned to Singapore"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 39.26,
    "endTime": 41.26,
    "text": "and, in 1990,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 41.26,
    "endTime": 43.26,
    "text": "performed Asia's first successful"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 43.26,
    "endTime": 46.26,
    "text": "cadaveric liver transplant procedure,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 46.26,
    "endTime": 49.26,
    "text": "but against all odds."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 49.26,
    "endTime": 51.26,
    "text": "Now when I look back,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 51.26,
    "endTime": 55.26,
    "text": "the transplant was actually the easiest part."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 55.26,
    "endTime": 59.26,
    "text": "Next, raising the money to fund the procedure."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 59.26,
    "endTime": 63.26,
    "text": "But perhaps the most challenging part"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 63.26,
    "endTime": 65.259,
    "text": "was to convince the regulators --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 65.26,
    "endTime": 69.26,
    "text": "a matter which was debated in the parliament --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 69.26,
    "endTime": 71.26,
    "text": "that a young female surgeon"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 71.26,
    "endTime": 73.26,
    "text": "be allowed the opportunity"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 73.26,
    "endTime": 76.26,
    "text": "to pioneer for her country."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 76.26,
    "endTime": 78.26,
    "text": "But 20 years on,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 78.26,
    "endTime": 80.26,
    "text": "my patient, Surinder,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 80.26,
    "endTime": 82.26,
    "text": "is Asia's longest surviving"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 82.26,
    "endTime": 85.26,
    "text": "cadaveric liver transplant to date."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 85.26,
    "endTime": 89.26,
    "text": "(Applause)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 89.26,
    "endTime": 92.26,
    "text": "And perhaps more important,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 92.26,
    "endTime": 94.26,
    "text": "I am the proud godmother"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 94.26,
    "endTime": 96.26,
    "text": "to her 14 year-old son."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 96.26,
    "endTime": 99.26,
    "text": "(Applause)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 100.26,
    "endTime": 102.26,
    "text": "But not all patients on the transplant wait list"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 102.26,
    "endTime": 104.26,
    "text": "are so fortunate."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 104.26,
    "endTime": 106.26,
    "text": "The truth is,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 106.26,
    "endTime": 108.26,
    "text": "there are just simply not enough donor organs"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 108.26,
    "endTime": 110.26,
    "text": "to go around."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 110.26,
    "endTime": 112.26,
    "text": "As the demand for donor organs"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 112.26,
    "endTime": 114.26,
    "text": "continues to rise,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 114.26,
    "endTime": 117.26,
    "text": "in large part due to the aging population,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 117.26,
    "endTime": 121.26,
    "text": "the supply has remained relatively constant."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 121.26,
    "endTime": 123.26,
    "text": "In the United States alone,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 123.26,
    "endTime": 127.26,
    "text": "100,000 men, women and children"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 127.26,
    "endTime": 130.25900000000001,
    "text": "are on the waiting list for donor organs,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 130.259,
    "endTime": 133.26,
    "text": "and more than a dozen die each day"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 133.26,
    "endTime": 136.26,
    "text": "because of a lack of donor organs."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 136.26,
    "endTime": 138.26,
    "text": "The transplant community"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 138.26,
    "endTime": 141.26,
    "text": "has actively campaigned in organ donation."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 141.26,
    "endTime": 143.26,
    "text": "And the gift of life"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 143.26,
    "endTime": 145.26,
    "text": "has been extended"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 145.26,
    "endTime": 147.26,
    "text": "from brain-dead donors"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 147.26,
    "endTime": 149.26,
    "text": "to living, related donors --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 149.26,
    "endTime": 152.26,
    "text": "relatives who might donate an organ"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 152.26,
    "endTime": 154.26,
    "text": "or a part of an organ,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 154.26,
    "endTime": 156.26,
    "text": "like a split liver graft,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 156.26,
    "endTime": 159.26,
    "text": "to a relative or loved one."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 159.26,
    "endTime": 162.26,
    "text": "But as there was still a dire shortage of donor organs,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 162.26,
    "endTime": 164.26,
    "text": "the gift of life was then extended"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 164.26,
    "endTime": 166.26,
    "text": "from living, related donors"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 166.26,
    "endTime": 169.26,
    "text": "to now living, unrelated donors."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 169.26,
    "endTime": 172.26,
    "text": "And this then has given rise"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 172.26,
    "endTime": 175.26,
    "text": "to unprecedented and unexpected"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 175.26,
    "endTime": 177.26,
    "text": "moral controversy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 178.26,
    "endTime": 181.26,
    "text": "How can one distinguish"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 181.26,
    "endTime": 184.26,
    "text": "a donation that is voluntary and altruistic"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 184.26,
    "endTime": 187.26,
    "text": "from one that is forced or coerced"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 187.26,
    "endTime": 189.26,
    "text": "from, for example,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 189.26,
    "endTime": 192.26,
    "text": "a submissive spouse, an in-law,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 192.26,
    "endTime": 194.26,
    "text": "a servant, a slave,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 194.26,
    "endTime": 196.26,
    "text": "an employee?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 196.26,
    "endTime": 199.26,
    "text": "Where and how can we draw the line?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 200.26,
    "endTime": 203.26,
    "text": "In my part of the world,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 203.26,
    "endTime": 206.26,
    "text": "too many people live below the poverty line."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 206.26,
    "endTime": 208.26,
    "text": "And in some areas,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 208.26,
    "endTime": 210.26,
    "text": "the commercial gifting of an organ"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 210.26,
    "endTime": 213.26,
    "text": "in exchange for monetary reward"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 213.26,
    "endTime": 215.26,
    "text": "has led to a flourishing trade"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 215.26,
    "endTime": 218.26,
    "text": "in living, unrelated donors."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 219.26,
    "endTime": 222.26,
    "text": "Shortly after I performed the first liver transplant,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 222.26,
    "endTime": 224.26,
    "text": "I received my next assignment,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 224.26,
    "endTime": 227.26,
    "text": "and that was to go to the prisons"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 227.26,
    "endTime": 229.26,
    "text": "to harvest organs"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 229.26,
    "endTime": 232.26,
    "text": "from executed prisoners."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 232.26,
    "endTime": 235.26,
    "text": "I was also pregnant at the time."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 235.26,
    "endTime": 237.26,
    "text": "Pregnancies are meant"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 237.26,
    "endTime": 240.26,
    "text": "to be happy and fulfilling moments"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 240.26,
    "endTime": 242.26,
    "text": "in any woman's life."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 242.26,
    "endTime": 244.26,
    "text": "But my joyful period"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 244.26,
    "endTime": 249.26,
    "text": "was marred by solemn and morbid thoughts --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 249.26,
    "endTime": 251.26,
    "text": "thoughts of walking through"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 251.26,
    "endTime": 254.26,
    "text": "the prison's high-security death row,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 254.26,
    "endTime": 256.26,
    "text": "as this was the only route"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 256.26,
    "endTime": 260.26,
    "text": "to take me to the makeshift operating room."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 260.26,
    "endTime": 262.26,
    "text": "And at each time,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 262.26,
    "endTime": 265.26,
    "text": "I would feel the chilling stares"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 265.26,
    "endTime": 269.26,
    "text": "of condemned prisoners' eyes follow me."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 269.26,
    "endTime": 271.26,
    "text": "And for two years,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 271.26,
    "endTime": 273.26,
    "text": "I struggled with the dilemma"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 273.26,
    "endTime": 275.26,
    "text": "of waking up at 4:30 am"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 275.26,
    "endTime": 277.26,
    "text": "on a Friday morning,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 277.26,
    "endTime": 279.26,
    "text": "driving to the prison,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 279.26,
    "endTime": 281.26,
    "text": "getting down, gloved and scrubbed,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 281.26,
    "endTime": 284.26,
    "text": "ready to receive the body"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 284.26,
    "endTime": 286.26,
    "text": "of an executed prisoner,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 286.26,
    "endTime": 288.26,
    "text": "remove the organs"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 288.26,
    "endTime": 290.26,
    "text": "and then transport these organs"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 290.26,
    "endTime": 292.26,
    "text": "to the recipient hospital"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 292.26,
    "endTime": 295.26,
    "text": "and then graft the gift of life"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 295.26,
    "endTime": 298.26,
    "text": "to a recipient the same afternoon."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 298.26,
    "endTime": 300.26,
    "text": "No doubt, I was informed,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 300.26,
    "endTime": 303.26,
    "text": "the consent had been obtained."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 306.26,
    "endTime": 308.26,
    "text": "But, in my life,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 308.26,
    "endTime": 313.26,
    "text": "the one fulfilling skill that I had"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 313.26,
    "endTime": 317.26,
    "text": "was now invoking feelings of conflict --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 317.26,
    "endTime": 319.26,
    "text": "conflict ranging"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 319.26,
    "endTime": 323.26,
    "text": "from extreme sorrow and doubt at dawn"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 323.26,
    "endTime": 325.26,
    "text": "to celebratory joy"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 325.26,
    "endTime": 329.26,
    "text": "at engrafting the gift of life at dusk."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 329.26,
    "endTime": 331.26,
    "text": "In my team,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 331.26,
    "endTime": 334.26,
    "text": "the lives of one or two of my colleagues"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 334.26,
    "endTime": 337.26,
    "text": "were tainted by this experience."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 337.26,
    "endTime": 340.26,
    "text": "Some of us may have been sublimated,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 340.26,
    "endTime": 344.26,
    "text": "but really none of us remained the same."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 344.26,
    "endTime": 347.26,
    "text": "I was troubled"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 347.26,
    "endTime": 351.26,
    "text": "that the retrieval of organs from executed prisoners"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 351.26,
    "endTime": 354.26,
    "text": "was at least as morally controversial"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 354.26,
    "endTime": 356.26,
    "text": "as the harvesting of stem cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 356.26,
    "endTime": 359.26,
    "text": "from human embryos."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 359.26,
    "endTime": 361.26,
    "text": "And in my mind,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 361.26,
    "endTime": 364.26,
    "text": "I realized as a surgical pioneer"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 364.26,
    "endTime": 367.26,
    "text": "that the purpose of my position of influence"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 367.26,
    "endTime": 369.26,
    "text": "was surely to speak up"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 369.26,
    "endTime": 372.26,
    "text": "for those who have no influence."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 372.26,
    "endTime": 374.26,
    "text": "It made me wonder"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 374.26,
    "endTime": 376.26,
    "text": "if there could be a better way --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 376.26,
    "endTime": 379.26,
    "text": "a way to circumvent death"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 379.26,
    "endTime": 381.26,
    "text": "and yet deliver the gift of life"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 381.26,
    "endTime": 384.26,
    "text": "that might exponentially impact"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 384.26,
    "endTime": 387.26,
    "text": "millions of patients worldwide."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 388.26,
    "endTime": 390.26,
    "text": "Now just about that time,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 390.26,
    "endTime": 392.26,
    "text": "the practice of surgery evolved"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 392.26,
    "endTime": 394.26,
    "text": "from big to small,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 394.26,
    "endTime": 396.26,
    "text": "from wide open incisions"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 396.26,
    "endTime": 398.26,
    "text": "to keyhole procedures,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 398.26,
    "endTime": 400.26,
    "text": "tiny incisions."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 401.26,
    "endTime": 404.26,
    "text": "And in transplantation, concepts shifted"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 404.26,
    "endTime": 407.26,
    "text": "from whole organs to cells."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 407.26,
    "endTime": 410.26,
    "text": "In 1988, at the University of Minnesota,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 410.26,
    "endTime": 413.26,
    "text": "I participated in a small series"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 413.26,
    "endTime": 416.26,
    "text": "of whole organ pancreas transplants."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 416.26,
    "endTime": 419.26,
    "text": "I witnessed the technical difficulty."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 419.26,
    "endTime": 421.26,
    "text": "And this inspired in my mind"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 421.26,
    "endTime": 425.26,
    "text": "a shift from transplanting whole organs"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 425.26,
    "endTime": 427.26,
    "text": "to perhaps transplanting cells."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 427.26,
    "endTime": 429.26,
    "text": "I thought to myself,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 429.26,
    "endTime": 432.26,
    "text": "why not take the individual cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 432.26,
    "endTime": 434.26,
    "text": "out of the pancreas --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 434.26,
    "endTime": 437.26,
    "text": "the cells that secrete insulin to cure diabetes --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 437.26,
    "endTime": 440.26,
    "text": "and transplant these cells? --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 440.26,
    "endTime": 442.26,
    "text": "technically a much simpler procedure"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 442.26,
    "endTime": 445.26,
    "text": "than having to grapple with the complexities"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 445.26,
    "endTime": 448.26,
    "text": "of transplanting a whole organ."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 448.26,
    "endTime": 450.26,
    "text": "And at that time,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 450.26,
    "endTime": 452.26,
    "text": "stem cell research"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 452.26,
    "endTime": 454.26,
    "text": "had gained momentum,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 454.26,
    "endTime": 457.26,
    "text": "following the isolation of the world's first"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 457.26,
    "endTime": 459.26,
    "text": "human embryonic stem cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 459.26,
    "endTime": 462.26,
    "text": "in the 1990s."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 462.26,
    "endTime": 465.26,
    "text": "The observation that stem cells, as master cells,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 465.26,
    "endTime": 467.26,
    "text": "could give rise"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 467.26,
    "endTime": 469.26,
    "text": "to a whole variety of different cell types --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 469.26,
    "endTime": 471.26,
    "text": "heart cells, liver cells,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 471.26,
    "endTime": 473.26,
    "text": "pancreatic islet cells --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 473.26,
    "endTime": 476.26,
    "text": "captured the attention of the media"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 476.26,
    "endTime": 479.26,
    "text": "and the imagination of the public."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 479.26,
    "endTime": 481.26,
    "text": "I too was fascinated"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 481.26,
    "endTime": 484.26,
    "text": "by this new and disruptive cell technology,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 484.26,
    "endTime": 487.26,
    "text": "and this inspired a shift in my mindset,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 487.26,
    "endTime": 489.26,
    "text": "from transplanting whole organs"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 489.26,
    "endTime": 492.26,
    "text": "to transplanting cells."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 492.26,
    "endTime": 495.26,
    "text": "And I focused my research on stem cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 495.26,
    "endTime": 497.26,
    "text": "as a possible source"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 497.26,
    "endTime": 499.26,
    "text": "for cell transplants."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 500.26,
    "endTime": 502.26,
    "text": "Today we realize"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 502.26,
    "endTime": 505.26,
    "text": "that there are many different types of stem cells."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 505.26,
    "endTime": 507.26,
    "text": "Embryonic stem cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 507.26,
    "endTime": 509.26,
    "text": "have occupied center stage,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 509.26,
    "endTime": 513.26,
    "text": "chiefly because of their pluripotency --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 513.26,
    "endTime": 516.26,
    "text": "that is their ease in differentiating"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 516.26,
    "endTime": 519.26,
    "text": "into a variety of different cell types."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 520.26,
    "endTime": 523.26,
    "text": "But the moral controversy"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 523.26,
    "endTime": 526.26,
    "text": "surrounding embryonic stem cells --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 526.26,
    "endTime": 528.26,
    "text": "the fact that these cells are derived"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 528.26,
    "endTime": 531.26,
    "text": "from five-day old human embryos --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 531.26,
    "endTime": 533.26,
    "text": "has encouraged research"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 533.26,
    "endTime": 536.26,
    "text": "into other types of stem cells."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 536.26,
    "endTime": 540.26,
    "text": "Now to the ridicule of my colleagues,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 540.26,
    "endTime": 542.26,
    "text": "I inspired my lab"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 542.26,
    "endTime": 545.26,
    "text": "to focus on what I thought"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 545.26,
    "endTime": 549.26,
    "text": "was the most non-controversial source of stem cells,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 549.26,
    "endTime": 552.26,
    "text": "adipose tissue, or fat, yes fat --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 552.26,
    "endTime": 555.26,
    "text": "nowadays available in abundant supply --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 556.26,
    "endTime": 560.26,
    "text": "you and I, I think, would be very happy to get rid of anyway."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 561.26,
    "endTime": 563.26,
    "text": "Fat-derived stem cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 563.26,
    "endTime": 565.26,
    "text": "are adult stem cells."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 565.26,
    "endTime": 567.26,
    "text": "And adult stem cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 567.26,
    "endTime": 569.26,
    "text": "are found in you and me --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 569.26,
    "endTime": 571.26,
    "text": "in our blood, in our bone marrow,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 571.26,
    "endTime": 574.26,
    "text": "in our fat, our skin and other organs."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 574.26,
    "endTime": 576.26,
    "text": "And as it turns out,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 576.26,
    "endTime": 578.26,
    "text": "fat is one of the best sources"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 578.26,
    "endTime": 580.26,
    "text": "of adult stem cells."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 580.26,
    "endTime": 582.26,
    "text": "But adult stem cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 582.26,
    "endTime": 585.26,
    "text": "are not embryonic stem cells."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 585.26,
    "endTime": 587.26,
    "text": "And here is the limitation:"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 587.26,
    "endTime": 590.26,
    "text": "adult stem cells are mature cells,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 590.26,
    "endTime": 593.26,
    "text": "and, like mature human beings,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 593.26,
    "endTime": 596.26,
    "text": "these cells are more restricted in their thought"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 596.26,
    "endTime": 599.26,
    "text": "and more restricted in their behavior"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 599.26,
    "endTime": 601.26,
    "text": "and are unable to give rise"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 601.26,
    "endTime": 604.26,
    "text": "to the wide variety of specialized cell types,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 604.26,
    "endTime": 606.26,
    "text": "as embryonic stem cells [can]."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 606.26,
    "endTime": 609.26,
    "text": "But in 2007,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 609.26,
    "endTime": 612.26,
    "text": "two remarkable individuals,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 612.26,
    "endTime": 614.26,
    "text": "Shinya Yamanaka of Japan"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 614.26,
    "endTime": 617.26,
    "text": "and Jamie Thomson of the United States,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 617.26,
    "endTime": 620.26,
    "text": "made an astounding discovery."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 620.26,
    "endTime": 622.26,
    "text": "They discovered"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 622.26,
    "endTime": 625.26,
    "text": "that adult cells, taken from you and me,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 625.26,
    "endTime": 628.26,
    "text": "could be reprogrammed"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 628.26,
    "endTime": 630.26,
    "text": "back into embryonic-like cells,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 630.26,
    "endTime": 633.26,
    "text": "which they termed IPS cells,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 633.26,
    "endTime": 638.26,
    "text": "or induced pluripotent stem cells."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 638.26,
    "endTime": 640.26,
    "text": "And so guess what,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 640.26,
    "endTime": 643.26,
    "text": "scientists around the world and in the labs"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 643.26,
    "endTime": 645.26,
    "text": "are racing"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 645.26,
    "endTime": 648.26,
    "text": "to convert aging adult cells --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 648.26,
    "endTime": 650.26,
    "text": "aging adult cells from you and me --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 650.26,
    "endTime": 653.26,
    "text": "they are racing to reprogram these cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 653.26,
    "endTime": 657.26,
    "text": "back into more useful IPS cells."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 658.26,
    "endTime": 660.26,
    "text": "And in our lab,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 660.26,
    "endTime": 662.26,
    "text": "we are focused on taking fat"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 662.26,
    "endTime": 664.26,
    "text": "and reprogramming"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 664.26,
    "endTime": 666.26,
    "text": "mounds of fat"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 666.26,
    "endTime": 670.26,
    "text": "into fountains of youthful cells --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 670.26,
    "endTime": 672.26,
    "text": "cells that we may use"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 672.26,
    "endTime": 674.26,
    "text": "to then form other,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 674.26,
    "endTime": 676.26,
    "text": "more specialized, cells,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 676.26,
    "endTime": 679.26,
    "text": "which one day may be used as cell transplants."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 680.26,
    "endTime": 683.26,
    "text": "If this research is successful,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 683.26,
    "endTime": 686.26,
    "text": "it may then reduce the need"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 686.26,
    "endTime": 688.26,
    "text": "to research and sacrifice"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 688.26,
    "endTime": 691.26,
    "text": "human embryos."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 692.26,
    "endTime": 695.26,
    "text": "Indeed, there is a lot of hype, but also hope"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 695.26,
    "endTime": 697.26,
    "text": "that the promise of stem cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 697.26,
    "endTime": 699.26,
    "text": "will one day provide cures"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 699.26,
    "endTime": 701.26,
    "text": "for a whole range of conditions."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 701.26,
    "endTime": 704.26,
    "text": "Heart disease, stroke, diabetes,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 704.26,
    "endTime": 706.26,
    "text": "spinal cord injury, muscular dystrophy,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 706.26,
    "endTime": 709.26,
    "text": "retinal eye diseases --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 709.26,
    "endTime": 711.26,
    "text": "are any of these conditions"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 711.26,
    "endTime": 714.26,
    "text": "relevant, personally, to you?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 714.26,
    "endTime": 717.26,
    "text": "In May 2006,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 717.26,
    "endTime": 720.26,
    "text": "something horrible happened to me."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 720.26,
    "endTime": 722.26,
    "text": "I was about to start a robotic operation,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 722.26,
    "endTime": 724.26,
    "text": "but stepping out of the elevator"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 724.26,
    "endTime": 727.26,
    "text": "into the bright and glaring lights of the operating room,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 727.26,
    "endTime": 729.26,
    "text": "I realized"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 729.26,
    "endTime": 731.26,
    "text": "that my left visual field"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 731.26,
    "endTime": 734.26,
    "text": "was fast collapsing into darkness."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 734.26,
    "endTime": 736.26,
    "text": "Earlier that week,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 736.26,
    "endTime": 738.26,
    "text": "I had taken a rather hard knock"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 738.26,
    "endTime": 741.26,
    "text": "during late spring skiing -- yes, I fell."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 741.26,
    "endTime": 743.26,
    "text": "And I started to see floaters and stars,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 743.26,
    "endTime": 745.26,
    "text": "which I casually dismissed"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 745.26,
    "endTime": 748.26,
    "text": "as too much high-altitude sun exposure."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 748.26,
    "endTime": 750.26,
    "text": "What happened to me"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 750.26,
    "endTime": 752.26,
    "text": "might have been catastrophic,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 752.26,
    "endTime": 754.26,
    "text": "if not for the fact"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 754.26,
    "endTime": 756.26,
    "text": "that I was in reach of good surgical access."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 756.26,
    "endTime": 758.26,
    "text": "And I had my vision restored,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 758.26,
    "endTime": 761.26,
    "text": "but not before a prolonged period of convalescence --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 761.26,
    "endTime": 763.26,
    "text": "three months --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 763.26,
    "endTime": 765.26,
    "text": "in a head down position."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 765.26,
    "endTime": 767.26,
    "text": "This experience"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 767.26,
    "endTime": 770.26,
    "text": "taught me to empathize more with my patients,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 770.26,
    "endTime": 773.26,
    "text": "and especially those with retinal diseases."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 774.26,
    "endTime": 776.26,
    "text": "37 million people worldwide"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 776.26,
    "endTime": 778.26,
    "text": "are blind,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 778.26,
    "endTime": 781.26,
    "text": "and 127 million more"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 781.26,
    "endTime": 784.26,
    "text": "suffer from impaired vision."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 784.26,
    "endTime": 787.26,
    "text": "Stem cell-derived retinal transplants,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 787.26,
    "endTime": 789.26,
    "text": "now in a research phase,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 789.26,
    "endTime": 791.26,
    "text": "may one day restore vision,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 791.26,
    "endTime": 793.26,
    "text": "or part vision,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 793.26,
    "endTime": 797.26,
    "text": "to millions of patients with retinal diseases worldwide."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 797.26,
    "endTime": 799.26,
    "text": "Indeed, we live"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 799.26,
    "endTime": 801.26,
    "text": "in both challenging"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 801.26,
    "endTime": 804.26,
    "text": "as well as exciting times."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 805.26,
    "endTime": 808.26,
    "text": "As the world population ages,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 808.26,
    "endTime": 810.26,
    "text": "scientists are racing"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 810.26,
    "endTime": 812.26,
    "text": "to discover new ways"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 812.26,
    "endTime": 814.26,
    "text": "to enhance the power of the body"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 814.26,
    "endTime": 817.26,
    "text": "to heal itself through stem cells."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 817.26,
    "endTime": 819.26,
    "text": "It is a fact"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 819.26,
    "endTime": 822.26,
    "text": "that when our organs or tissues are injured,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 822.26,
    "endTime": 824.26,
    "text": "our bone marrow"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 824.26,
    "endTime": 826.26,
    "text": "releases stem cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 826.26,
    "endTime": 828.26,
    "text": "into our circulation."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 828.26,
    "endTime": 830.26,
    "text": "And these stem cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 830.26,
    "endTime": 832.26,
    "text": "then float in the bloodstream"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 832.26,
    "endTime": 835.26,
    "text": "and hone in to damaged organs"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 835.26,
    "endTime": 837.26,
    "text": "to release growth factors"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 837.26,
    "endTime": 839.26,
    "text": "to repair the damaged tissue."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 839.26,
    "endTime": 842.26,
    "text": "Stem cells may be used as building blocks"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 842.26,
    "endTime": 846.26,
    "text": "to repair damaged scaffolds within our body,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 846.26,
    "endTime": 848.26,
    "text": "or to provide new liver cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 848.26,
    "endTime": 851.26,
    "text": "to repair damaged liver."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 851.26,
    "endTime": 854.26,
    "text": "As we speak, there are 117 or so clinical trials"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 854.26,
    "endTime": 857.26,
    "text": "researching the use of stem cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 857.26,
    "endTime": 859.26,
    "text": "for liver diseases."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 859.26,
    "endTime": 861.26,
    "text": "What lies ahead?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 861.26,
    "endTime": 863.26,
    "text": "Heart disease"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 863.26,
    "endTime": 865.26,
    "text": "is the leading cause of death worldwide."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 865.26,
    "endTime": 867.26,
    "text": "1.1 million Americans"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 867.26,
    "endTime": 870.26,
    "text": "suffer heart attacks yearly."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 870.26,
    "endTime": 872.26,
    "text": "4.8 million"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 872.26,
    "endTime": 874.26,
    "text": "suffer cardiac failure."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 874.26,
    "endTime": 876.26,
    "text": "Stem cells may be used"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 876.26,
    "endTime": 878.26,
    "text": "to deliver growth factors"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 878.26,
    "endTime": 880.26,
    "text": "to repair damaged heart muscle"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 880.26,
    "endTime": 882.26,
    "text": "or be differentiated"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 882.26,
    "endTime": 884.26,
    "text": "into heart muscle cells"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 884.26,
    "endTime": 886.26,
    "text": "to restore heart function."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 886.26,
    "endTime": 889.26,
    "text": "There are 170 clinical trials"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 889.26,
    "endTime": 893.26,
    "text": "investigating the role of stem cells in heart disease."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 893.26,
    "endTime": 896.26,
    "text": "While still in a research phase,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 896.26,
    "endTime": 899.26,
    "text": "stem cells may one day herald"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 899.26,
    "endTime": 902.26,
    "text": "a quantum leap in the field of cardiology."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 903.26,
    "endTime": 906.26,
    "text": "Stem cells provide hope for new beginnings --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 906.26,
    "endTime": 909.26,
    "text": "small, incremental steps,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 909.26,
    "endTime": 912.26,
    "text": "cells rather than organs,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 912.26,
    "endTime": 915.26,
    "text": "repair rather than replacement."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 915.26,
    "endTime": 918.26,
    "text": "Stem cell therapies"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 918.26,
    "endTime": 922.26,
    "text": "may one day reduce the need for donor organs."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 922.26,
    "endTime": 924.26,
    "text": "Powerful new technologies"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 924.26,
    "endTime": 926.26,
    "text": "always present enigmas."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 926.26,
    "endTime": 928.26,
    "text": "As we speak,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 928.26,
    "endTime": 931.26,
    "text": "the world's first human embryonic stem cell trial for spinal cord injury"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 931.26,
    "endTime": 933.26,
    "text": "is currently underway"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 933.26,
    "endTime": 936.26,
    "text": "following the USFDA approval."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 936.26,
    "endTime": 938.26,
    "text": "And in the U.K.,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 938.26,
    "endTime": 940.26,
    "text": "neural stem cells to treat stroke"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 940.26,
    "endTime": 943.26,
    "text": "are being investigated in a phase one trial."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 944.26,
    "endTime": 947.26,
    "text": "The research success that we celebrate today"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 947.26,
    "endTime": 949.26,
    "text": "has been made possible"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 949.26,
    "endTime": 953.26,
    "text": "by the curiosity and contribution and commitment"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 953.26,
    "endTime": 955.26,
    "text": "of individual scientists"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 955.26,
    "endTime": 957.26,
    "text": "and medical pioneers."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 957.26,
    "endTime": 960.26,
    "text": "Each one has his story."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 960.26,
    "endTime": 963.26,
    "text": "My story has been about my journey"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 963.26,
    "endTime": 965.26,
    "text": "from organs to cells --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 965.26,
    "endTime": 967.26,
    "text": "a journey through controversy,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 967.26,
    "endTime": 969.26,
    "text": "inspired by hope --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 969.26,
    "endTime": 972.26,
    "text": "hope that, as we age,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 972.26,
    "endTime": 975.26,
    "text": "you and I may one day celebrate longevity"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 975.26,
    "endTime": 977.26,
    "text": "with an improved quality of life."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 977.26,
    "endTime": 979.26,
    "text": "Thank you."
  }
]